.SH SHFindLWin
Determine the spherical\-harmonic bandwidth that is necessary to achieve
a certain concentration factor.
.SH Usage
\f[CR]lwin\f[R] = SHFindLWin (\f[CR]theta0\f[R], \f[CR]m\f[R],
\f[CR]alpha\f[R], \f[CR]taper_number\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]lwin\f[R] : output, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic bandwidth
.TP
\f[CR]theta0\f[R] : input, real(dp)
The angular radius of the spherical cap in radians.
.TP
\f[CR]m\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The angular order of the taper.
.TP
\f[CR]alpha\f[R] : input, real(dp)
The desired concentration factor of the window.
This must lie between 0 and 1.
.TP
\f[CR]taper_number\f[R] : optional, input, integer(int32), default = 1
The taper number corresponding to the angular order \f[CR]m\f[R].
The default is to use the first taper.
.SH Description
\f[CR]SHFindLWin\f[R] will determine the spherical harmonic bandwidth
that is required for a window of the spherical\-cap concentration
problem to achive a certain concentration factor.
By default, the first taper corresponding to the angular order
\f[CR]m\f[R] will be used, but this can be modified by specifying the
optional argument \f[CR]taper_number\f[R].
.SH References
Wieczorek, M. A. and F. J. Simons, Localized spectral analysis on the
sphere, Geophys.
J. Int., 162, 655\-675, 2005.
